Incident.Summary: Facebook video reveals assault where firearms are displayed.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Reason for Submission: CED Initial Narrative: On January 2, 2024, Investigators from the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division were notified of a video circulating on Facebook from an assault that occurred on December 31, 2023, in the area of Bratten Avenue, Princess Anne, Somerset County, Maryland. base64," style="height:437px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> During an open-source intelligence gathering search, I located the account identified as text-decoration:underline">https://www.facebook.com/fukumean.itzmeka.7, the display name was identified as Shemeka Hills and viewed the video. The video provides audible and visual depictions. A preservation was sent to Facebook c/o Meta Platforms for the account and video. Based on my experience in Somerset County, I know the area depicted in the video to be located on Bratten Avenue, Princess Anne, Maryland. This location is directly behind the Sommers Place Apartment Complex, and adjacent to the building identified as 11408 Bratten Avenue. While viewing the video, I observed the following individuals and their depicted actions: I observe a crowd of people gathered at this location I observe an altercation between Shawn Ricki Wallace [hereinafter referred to as Wallace] and Gregory Ikeem Isaac Boyd [hereinafter referred to as Boyd] I observe Boyd chest bump Wallace Wallace strikes Boyd with closed fist causing Boyd to fall to the ground The subjects move to the roadway as a subject identified as Taysheik Boyd-Charles [hereinafter referred to as Taysheik] wearing a black hooded sweatshirt with a large white symbol on the back moves toward Wallace aggressively striking Wallace in the back of the head with closed fist Wallace proceeds to fall to the ground as he is struck by Tayshiek, Boyd, and a subject identified as Amere Jhontu Rashon Lee-Waters [hereinafter referred to as Amere] During the altercation, Taysheik removes a black semi-automatic handgun with extended magazine from his waist band and begins displaying the handgun as I observe him rack the slide. I can audibly hear the mechanical metal mechanisms activate from the slide movement. I observe remove a black semi-automatic handgun with extended magazine from his fanny pack that is worn across his chest. I observe Boyd continuously strike Wallace in the face with closed fist Amere walks toward the crowd while carrying the handgun in his right hand screaming whose riding for this nigger An adult female attempts to separate Boyd from Wallace while calling the subject Greg Amere walks toward the subject recording the incident as a male subject says Amere as he turns and faces the camera. While Wallace is lying on the ground, he appears unconscious, Taysheik steps over his body while the handgun is pointed at Wallace on the ground. margin-left:8px">I observe a subject identified as Tywan Aaron Johnson [hereinafter referred to as Johnson] attempt to get Wallaces limp body off the ground Based on my observations, I conducted a search of the call history for the area for December 31, 2023, and January 1, 2024. On January 1, 2024, Troopers from the Maryland State Police Princess Anne Barrack and Princess Anne Emergency Medical Services responded to 30512 Nutters Lane, Apartment 15, Princess Anne, Maryland for a victim of a previous assault. Upon arrival, Tfc. Wilson made contact with the caller who identified that her son Shawn Wallace had been assaulted previously in the Greenwood area and was transported to Tidal Health Peninsula Regional prior to his arrival. Tfc. Wilson made contact with Wallace at the hospital. Wallace would not provide any details about the incident. I made contact with the property management from Sommers Place Apartment Complex and received permission to review the camera footage from the apartment complex. Based on the sun setting and shadows in the video the time was estimated to be approximately 1630hrs. While reviewing the camera footage, I observed the following depictions: I was able to determine the incident occurred on December 31, 2023, at approximately 1627hrs. I observed Tyshiek, Boyd, and Waters enter the complex from the southeast corner of the complex and begin walking along the sidewalk at approximately 1628hrs. I observe Waters enter 11408 Bratten Avenue, Apartment 23. I observed Tysheik start toward the door of Apartment 23 and then divert to a black BMW passenger car parked in front of Apartment 23 alongside the sidewalk. Tysheik opened the drivers door of the vehicle. Taysheik partially enters the vehicle and then quickly exits the vehicle. Waters exits apartment 23, and Boyd, Waters and Tayshiek walk south in the complex toward the southeast corner out of camera view. The three subjects re-appear on screen and begin walking toward the northeast corner of the complex toward the vehicle entrance. As they approach the entrance, I observed them begin to run back toward Bratten Avenue margin-left:8px">I observed Wallace and Johnson enter the camera view from Bratten Avenue. Johnson and an unknown male subject are assisting Wallace toward the northwest corner of the complex. I have requested a copy of the surveillance footage from the complex to be downloaded through Safehouse, LLC the holders of the security system contract for the complex. On January 5, 2023, while conducting surveillance in the Sommers Place Apartment Complex, I located the black BMW previously identified as the vehicle Taysheik enters after the incident, parked in front of Apartment 23. I identified the Virginia registration as TLY8830, a registration check revealed the vehicle is registered to Barbara Ann Charles who is associated with apartment 23. A check with the Maryland Gun Center was conducted and revealed Amere and Taysheik are prohibited from possessing firearms due to previous criminal charges. Amere Jhontu Rashon Lee-Waters is prohibited from possessing firearms due to the below listed reasons: Prohibiting Offense(s): Handgun in Vehicle Conviction Date: 8/21/2022 State: Maryland Court: District Case#: D-022-CR-22-000402 Taysheik Hadeem Boyd-Charles is prohibited from possessing firearms due to the below listed reasons: Prohibiting Offense(s): Assault Second Degree Conviction Date: 6/10/2019 State: Maryland County: Somerset Court: Circuit Case#: 19-K-15-010604 A residential check with property management revealed the listed tenant is identified as Cleo Yalanda Williamena Charles [hereinafter referred to as Cleo]. An additional MVA check revealed, Cleo, Taysheik and Boyd utilized 11408 Bratten Avenue, Apartment 23, as their address on record. Below are screenshots from the Facebook video with captions identifying subjects and their actions: Subject identified as Amere Jhontu Rashon Lee-Waters. base64," style="height:1412px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Subject identified as Taysheik Hadeem Boyd-Charles base64," style="height:2085px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> During the argument, Boyd chest bumps Wallace and Wallace with closed fist strikes Boyd, knocking him to the ground. base64," style="height:867px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Boyd gets up and begins to approach Wallace as they enter Bratten Avenue. Wallace is approached by Taysheik. Taysheik strikes Wallace in the back of the head with closed fist causing Walace to hit the ground. base64," style="height:875px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Boyd, Waters, and Taysheik begin to strike Wallace with closed fist blows to the face. Taysheik displays a handgun from his waist band. base64," style="height:1763px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Taysheik activates the metallic slide on the firearm. base64," style="height:1744px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Waters displays a handgun from his cross-shoulder bag that is displayed on his chest. Waters begins yelling at the crowd saying whose riding for this nigger repeatedly as he walks toward the crowd of people observing the incident. base64," style="height:1099px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Boyd continues to assault Wallace an adult female attempts to protect Wallace and begins arguing with Boyd. The female identifies the subject as Greg while yelling at him. base64," style="height:1043px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Waters walks toward the camera and a male subject says Amere as he turns toward the camera. base64," style="height:926px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> At the conclusion of the assault Tywan Johnson [hereinafter referred to as Johnson] attempts to get Wallace from the ground, but he appears to be unconscious. base64," style="height:842px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> Case Open.

Reason for Submission: Residential Vehicle Search Warrant Arrest Warrant(s) Narrative: On January 12, 2024, I authored a residential search warrant for 11408 Bratten Avenue, Apt 23, Princess Anne, Maryland as well the black 2006 BMW bearing Virginia registration TLY8830. The warrants were reviewed and signed by the Honorable Judge Paula A. Price of the Somerset County District Court. On January 17, 2024, I submitted applications for charges for Amere Jhontu Rashon Lee-Waters and Taysheik Hadeem Boyd-Charles to the Somerset County District Court Commissioners Office. The commissioner issued arrest warrants for both subjects with the following charges: Assault - First Degree Assault Second Degree Reckless Endangerment Handgun on Person Loaded Handgun on Person Firearm Use/Fel-Viol Crime Reg Firearm: Illegal Possession margin-left:8px">Disorderly Conduct Case Open, pending warrant services.

Supplement #1: On 01/01/2024 at 0429 hours, I TFC. Wilson #6689 responded to 30512 Nutters Lane Apt 15, Princess Anne, MD 21853. Somerset Central contacted the MSP Princess Anne barracks and advised a female caller at that residence contacted 911 requesting EMS for her son who was assaulted on 12/31/2023 at approximately 1500 hours. Upon my arrival, I observed the ambulance already leaving the scene. I made contact with Scherrie Elizabeth Wallace (1F,DOB:08/03/1978), outside of her apartment. Wallace advised her son, Shawn Ricki Wallace (1M, DOB: 09/02/1998), had been jumped yesterday at around 1500 or 1600 hours. Scherrie Wallace could only advise her son had been jumped in the hood, as she pointed over towards Sommers Place apartments. Scherrie said she did not know any other details about the assault and advised her son most likely will not provide me with any information. At 0510 hours I responded to Tidal Health in Salisbury to make contact with Shawn Wallace. Wallace was located in the patient triage waiting area section of the emergency room. I noticed Wallaces right eye to be swollen shut from what appeared to be a recent physical injury. I advised Wallace why I was there, and he stated he did not want to provide any information on how or where he obtained his injuries. I told Wallace if he was not willing to provide any information then I would not be able to complete a police report regarding the matter. Wallace acknowledged and said he was not going to provide any details. All events occurred in Somerset/Wicomico County, MD.
